sect1.para:
Most families place a high priority on self-identification. To deny the African heritage or self as of the Black race is most offensive. The experiences of the Black race have improved in that more of them are college educated, employed in white collar positions, business owners, and live in the upper echelon of neighborhoods. Despite these improvements, African Americans remain in the “blue collar” segment of the working class. Nevertheless, they are mindful of where they came from by celebrating their African American (Black) heritage every year in February. But if you ask a Black person about the celebration, they will say, “Every day of the year should be celebrated by each person who is of the Black race” (Satterfield 
               2023
            ).
